               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1510" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1510" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1510" type="surname" value="DOHERTY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1510" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>MICHAEL DOHERTY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Bell-alley. I had the articles stated, in my box, I broke the key of it a fortnight or three weeks before the 6th of April, and I gave the articles stated, in charge of the prisoner's wife, who lived in the same house—I missed the trowsers, the coats, and other things—they are now here—the pawnbroker has them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1511" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1511" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1511" type="surname" value="GOODE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1511" type="given" value="JOSEPH JOHN"></interp>JOSEPH JOHN GOODE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a a pawnbroker. I have two coats and a pair of trowsers, which I took in of the prisoner on the 6th of April, which he said were his own property—it was between four and six o'clock.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I pawned them; I went out that morning at six o'clock to work; the prosecutor took my wife and made her drunk; and when I came home I found him and my wife in the act of adultery. I went to the fire, took up the poker, and gave him a pretty good share of it. I went out, and when I returned I asked my wife for some money; the prosecutor said I might take some clothes, and make money, which I did.; and in the evening he got sorry about letting me have them; he asked me for the money, and the money was scattered between them.</p>
